# Nido Perunilas - Kindergarten Website

This is the official website for Nido Perunilas, a kindergarten located in Lima, Per√∫. The website is built with Astro, using Tailwind CSS and DaisyUI for a friendly, child-oriented design.

## Project Purpose

The website serves as a comprehensive information platform for parents and guardians, featuring:
- Information about the kindergarten's programs and services
- Contact forms for inquiries and registrations
- News and updates about activities
- Photo galleries and event information
- Resources for parents

## Key Directories

- `src/pages/` - Contains all route components and pages (in Spanish)
- `src/components/` - Reusable UI components with child-friendly design
- `src/layouts/` - Page layouts and templates
- `src/content/` - Content collections and MDX files (in Spanish)
- `src/styles/` - Global styles and theme configuration
- `public/` - Static assets served directly
- `public/assets/` - All media assets (images, videos, documents)

## Important Files

- [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs) - Astro configuration including MDX, RSS, and sitemap plugins
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
- [src/content.config.ts](mdc:src/content.config.ts) - Content collection configuration
- [src/consts.ts](mdc:src/consts.ts) - Project constants and configuration

## Design Guidelines

- Use DaisyUI themes as the primary styling system
- Implement pastel colors and child-friendly design elements
- Maintain a clean, professional look while being approachable
- Ensure all content is in Spanish
- Optimize for both desktop and mobile viewing
- Follow accessibility guidelines for better user experience

## Development

The project uses the following key technologies:
- Astro v5.8.0 for the framework
- Tailwind CSS v4.1.7 for custom styling when needed
- DaisyUI v5.0.37 for UI components and theming
- MDX for content authoring

Common development commands:
- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run preview` - Preview production build

## Content Language

All content must be written in Spanish, including:
- Page content
- Component text
- Form labels and messages
- Metadata and SEO content
- Documentation and comments



